<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.figma.com/community/plugin/1062137197474406566/Scrim-That">Scrim That Figma Plugin</a><br />Quickly add a scrim over a selected layer in Figma Design with the <em>Scrim That</em> plugin with just one click.</li>
</ul>
Strips/Highlight Technique
<p>The <strong>strips/highlight</strong> is one of the simplest design techniques that you can apply to your design. Add a semi-transparent black (or dark-colored) rectangle strip over the image along with your text, or you can be bolder and use different colors instead. But always make sure that the colors you selected for the fonts and the graphic elements have a lot of contrast against the background!</p>
<p><img src="https://files.smashing.media/articles/designing-accessible-text-over-images-part1/smashing-text-over-images-technique-strips.jpg" /></p>
<h3>Examples From The Wild</h3>
